# ZAZAZA.app Development Rules

## Project Structure
Games are organized by category folders under app/
- app/brain-age/ → Brain Tests (type: "brain")
- app/office-iq/ → Games (type: "game")
- app/korean-tv/ → Games (type: "game")
- app/dark-personality/ → Personality (type: "personality")
- app/relationship/ → Personality (type: "personality")
- app/money/ → Personality (type: "personality")
- app/focus-test/ → Brain Tests (type: "brain")
- app/word-iq/ → Brain Tests (type: "brain")

## Adding a New Game
1. Create game file at app/[category]/[game-id]/page.tsx
2. Add entry to content/games.json with ALL these fields:
   - id, category, type, title, subtitle, description
   - hasLeaderboard: true/false
3. category must match the folder name exactly
4. type must be: "brain", "game", or "personality"

## Adding a New Category
If a new category is needed (e.g. "ugc", "send-fun"):
1. Create folder under app/[new-category]/
2. Add category metadata to games.json categories array
3. Add type mapping in app/page.tsx filter logic
4. Use a new color accent (do not reuse existing colors)

## Existing Patterns - Always Follow
- Use existing hooks: getRank, saveHighScore, generateResultCard
- Use InterstitialAd component for ad placement
- Use trackPlay(gameId) when game starts (fire and forget)
- Use LeaderboardSection component if hasLeaderboard: true
- Match existing Tailwind styling and component structure
- Never invent new patterns — always check existing games first

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Supabase for leaderboard and play tracking (lib/supabase.ts, lib/tracking.ts)
- Deployed on Vercel via GitHub
- Single source of truth for games: content/games.json

## Fun Sends (`/send`)
- Card art lives in `public/cards/<category>/` (e.g. `i-love-you/`, `birthday/`, `roast/`, `etc/`). Images are auto-discovered at build time.
- Optional per-file labels/face defaults: `FUN_SEND_CARD_OVERRIDES` in `lib/funSendTemplates.ts` (keys: `category/filename`).
- Loader: `lib/loadFunSendCategoryTemplates.ts`

## Key Files
- content/games.json → all game metadata
- app/page.tsx → main page only
- lib/tracking.ts → trackPlay, saveToLeaderboard, getLeaderboard
- lib/supabase.ts → Supabase client
- components/LeaderboardSection.tsx → reusable leaderboard UI

## Never Touch Without Good Reason
- app/layout.tsx
- lib/supabase.ts
- Any game page when working on main page or vice versa

## Score Direction
- Higher score = better (default)
- If lower = better (e.g. time-based), store as (maxTime - timeTaken)
  so getRank logic stays consistent

## Leaderboard
- hasLeaderboard: true → show LeaderboardSection on result screen
- hasLeaderboard: false → personality/type tests, no leaderboard
- trackPlay() fires on game start, never blocks UI
